The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 HCL Info net profit dips 17% to Rs 27 cr

 OUR CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, Aug. 23: HCL Infosystems Ltds net profit after tax dropped 17 per cent to Rs 26.88 crore for the quarter ended June 30 from Rs 32.42 crore a year ago. Total income went up to Rs 598.69 crore from Rs 537.22 crore, a jump of 11.4 per cent. 

 HCLs net profit after tax for the year ended June 30 was Rs 113.22 crore compared with Rs 132.77 crore in the previous year, an almost 14.7 per cent decline. 

 Total income went up to Rs 2,300.56 crore from Rs 1,963.91 crore, a rise of 17.14 per cent.

 The groups net profit after tax was Rs 70.30 crore for the quarter ended June 30, against Rs 59.04 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year. 

 Total income increased to Rs 3,098.22 crore from Rs 2,205.19 crore. 

 The group has posted a net profit after tax of Rs 280.36 crore for the year ended June 30, compared with Rs 227.70 crore a year ago. 

 Total income has increased to Rs 11,387.72 crore from Rs 7,788.58 crore. 

 On July 13, HCL Infosystems had unveiled a range of infrastructure technology solutions aimed at the Indian BPO and ITeS sector. 

 The range includes a specially designed personal computer called HCL BPO PC, which enables the operation of one PC in two securely isolated work environments and holds the potential to reduce IT spending per seat and infrastructure cost of a BPO centre.




